Description: In-kernel QUIC protocol implementation (DKMS source)
 The quic kernel module provides an in-kernel implementation of the
 QUIC transport protocol (RFC 9000) for Linux. It exposes a new socket
 family (IPPROTO_QUIC) so that user-space applications, and kernel
 consumers such as SMB and NFS, can use QUIC with familiar socket
 semantics. The TLS handshake itself is delegated to user space (for
 example via tlshd from ktls-utils).
 .
 This package contains the source for the quic.ko module. DKMS will
 automatically build and install the module against any installed
 kernel that has matching kernel headers.
 .
 Upstream project: https://github.com/lxin/quic
